        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=78164&amp;TOPIC_ID=9014&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=HP+%26gt%3B+All%3F+More+like+HP+%26gt%3B+Thinking&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I havent read the whole thread, but here goes my opinion:</P><P>HP > all. Not because HP = mana, which is not. FT = mana to be accurate. Im hadly OOM ever, so I tend to max HP. </P><P>Why is HP > all? because EQ is a melee driven game. 90% of the dmg taken in EQ is melee wise, hence HP is the best protection you can have. Dont you feel more secure when you solo exp with Aego on? I personally do. More HP is a life saver, plain and simple. Oh and if you say you dont get it, I recommend you stop root/dotting in Akheva or Fear Kite in Katta. If you are one of those people that like to push your limits a bit further, trying funky pulls or adventure deep into a dungeon for higher reward, HP will save your butt A LOT.</P><P>I couldnt think of any better life insurance in EQ than a pure raw large hp pool.</P><P>On a side note, I believe that regen is VERY over rated. Once you reach a fairly decent HP pool, you dont notice the loss of HP due to lich so much, and Vexing works just fine.</P><P>----------------------<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62873" target="_blank">Yaguex</a>, warlock, <a href="http://www.mortalis.com/" target="_blank">Mortalis</a>, Antonius Bayle.<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
